    "Liu et al. (2021) introduced the Swin Transformer in the same year, addressing the challenges related to applying the Transformer from the language domain to the visual domain, such as the significant difference in the scale of visual entities and the high pixel resolution of images compared to words in text.",
    "As shown in Fig. 23, this illustration presents two consecutive Swin Transformer blocks, where W-MSA and SW-MSA have multi-head attention modules with regular and shifted window configurations, respectively.",
    "Swin Transformer introduces a hierarchical Transformer structure, utilizing shifted windows for computing representations.",
    "In various tasks, the experimental results have significantly surpassed previous state-of-the-art models, demonstrating the potential of Transformer-based models as visual backbone networks.",
    "Although Swin Transformer has linear computational complexity,it may face issues such as memory limitations for particularly large image inputs."
